HEADWORD: lend-lease
<hw>lend-lease</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the temporary transfer of goods
and services to an ally to aid in a common cause; <as>as,
<ex>lend-lease</ex> during World War II was extremely
generous</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lease-lend.</syn>⟦br⟧
